rrow has 35% plasma cells.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.089793,0.15308,0.13853,0.10791,0.094836,0.08829,0.074864,0.069213,0.058191,0.048816,0.041183,0.035295],"unified_progress":[0.0756,0.11318,0.11829,0.10919,0.10612,0.098135,0.086802,0.07991,0.069468,0.057356,0.047554,0.038392]},{"section":4,"text":"Hmm.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.35512,0.061334,0.060976,0.067969,0.064945,0.062195,0.056947,0.060829,0.059303,0.053753,0.054986,0.041648],"unified_progress":[0.2308,0.093795,0.071666,0.067439,0.078429,0.073147,0.086178,0.075403,0.069704,0.055465,0.050523,0.047447]},{"section":5,"text":"First, hypercalcemia can be from bone issues.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.084366,0.17593,0.065801,0.10565,0.092815,0.096089,0.079394,0.071764,0.065426,0.059835,0.054398,0.048534],"unified_progress":[0.085061,0.10007,0.064522,0.095038,0.09215,0.10182,0.091285,0.085485,0.08167,0.077513,0.070179,0.055211]},{"section":6,"text":"The skeletal destruction on X-rays makes me think of something affecting the bones, like metastases or maybe a bone marrow disorder.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.048271,0.091567,0.1046,0.10527,0.10203,0.096269,0.092345,0.084157,0.080225,0.074832,0.063659,0.05678],"unified_progress":[0.047041,0.072832,0.086811,0.097299,0.098977,0.098645,0.096715,0.09276,0.090348,0.085421,0.07337,0.05978]},{"section":7,"text":"The M spike suggests a monoclonal protein, which is typical for conditions like multiple myeloma, Waldenstr\u00f6m's macroglobulinemia, or maybe lymphoma.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037659,0.076577,0.092152,0.10215,0.10536,0.10227,0.1001,0.091674,0.082464,0.082504,0.066823,0.060269],"unified_progress":[0.037984,0.063337,0.083638,0.094295,0.099349,0.11003,0.10333,0.098605,0.092648,0.087858,0.072069,0.056865]},{"section":8,"text":"Plasmacytoma is a tumor of plasma cells.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035586,0.072345,0.085318,0.096029,0.10143,0.10229,0.10165,0.094274,0.088735,0.086819,0.071103,0.064427],"unified_progress":[0.039822,0.062017,0.08169,0.095105,0.10054,0.10644,0.10339,0.099773,0.095357,0.086517,0.071301,0.058045]},{"section":9,"text":"There are two types: solitary and multiple.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029082,0.066031,0.082176,0.093337,0.10019,0.1027,0.10292,0.097646,0.092317,0.091088,0.076302,0.06622],"unified_progress":[0.048494,0.066942,0.081626,0.0921,0.096873,0.10396,0.10046,0.098836,0.09353,0.087983,0.071918,0.057274]},{"section":10,"text":"If there's only one, it's solitary, but if there are more, that's multiple myeloma.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03326,0.070757,0.083006,0.0912,0.095824,0.099032,0.099121,0.09603,0.09278,0.090389,0.078229,0.070371],"unified_progress":[0.045649,0.072222,0.083844,0.091596,0.095439,0.098797,0.096852,0.096521,0.092891,0.087975,0.075198,0.063015]},{"section":11,"text":"The bone marrow showing 35% plasma cells is a key point.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038105,0.079511,0.092989,0.097648,0.096263,0.094685,0.094435,0.089901,0.090221,0.083758,0.075264,0.067221],"unified_progress":[0.041634,0.075326,0.089542,0.098226,0.10244,0.099518,0.098159,0.092802,0.09097,0.08194,0.071399,0.058047]},{"section":12,"text":"I remember that in multiple myeloma, having over 10% plasma cells is a criterion, but 35% is way higher.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040664,0.079385,0.091381,0.097374,0.098687,0.096748,0.096326,0.091278,0.085077,0.083351,0.073117,0.066613],"unified_progress":[0.046065,0.072596,0.086886,0.094959,0.099349,0.10258,0.1014,0.093517,0.08786,0.082364,0.072221,0.060205]},{"section":13,"text":"Also, the presence of end-organ damage like renal failure (which can be from myeloma light chains damaging the kidneys) and hypercalcemia (from bone lesions releasing calcium) fits.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031218,0.066743,0.079313,0.088678,0.095933,0.099858,0.10252,0.098422,0.093955,0.089655,0.082258,0.071445],"unified_progress":[0.035755,0.057915,0.074018,0.081011,0.090799,0.10018,0.099367,0.099589,0.099837,0.097281,0.091003,0.073246]},{"section":14,"text":"The M spike is the monoclonal band seen in serum electrophoresis, which is common in myeloma.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037666,0.073635,0.085861,0.093354,0.096539,0.096313,0.098051,0.093978,0.089376,0.086965,0.077767,0.070495],"unified_progress":[0.042449,0.064954,0.081625,0.090227,0.097132,0.099724,0.10226,0.096671,0.093126,0.087903,0.078474,0.065456]},{"section":15,"text":"The combination of all these: plasmacytoma, high plasma cells in marrow, hypercalcemia, renal issues, and the M spike points towards multiple myeloma.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031575,0.064966,0.07802,0.085893,0.090726,0.093114,0.095821,0.093909,0.094857,0.094311,0.090661,0.086148],"unified_progress":[0.036747,0.058617,0.073766,0.083382,0.090724,0.097567,0.097396,0.097829,0.098493,0.095992,0.090682,0.078805]},{"section":16,"text":"The 35% is definitely over the threshold.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03674,0.073317,0.085919,0.090818,0.091666,0.090862,0.092609,0.090962,0.090307,0.089055,0.084456,0.083289],"unified_progress":[0.043755,0.06701,0.078836,0.086894,0.091967,0.092742,0.095269,0.092961,0.092388,0.090157,0.08717,0.080853]},{"section":17,"text":"I don't think Waldenstr\u00f6m's would have such high plasma cells.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03264,0.066535,0.079156,0.087477,0.09275,0.095144,0.097953,0.096718,0.094093,0.093296,0.085538,0.078701],"unified_progress":[0.038475,0.062397,0.076394,0.085323,0.09197,0.096648,0.098033,0.098174,0.096307,0.0958